Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Small animals such as chicks, ducklings, mice, and baby turtles are not uncommon vehicles for salmonellosis for 2 reasons: they are small enough to handle and they carry salmonellae. Two ways to minimize the risk: aggressive hand washing after contact and choose other pets such as dogs or cats. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1hiS.]
